# GitHub Actions

This project uses [GitHub actions](https://docs.github.com/en/actions) as CI/CD Pipeline. The following workflows are available:
{% if use_terraform %}

- **terraform** - Lints and plans Terraform for both environments; applies production on push to `main`, or a manually-selected environment via workflow dispatch.
{% endif %}
{% if ansible_enabled %}

- **ansible** - Lints the playbook and syntax-checks it against each environment's inventory (staging, production).
{% endif %}

## Workflow secrets

The following workflow secrets must be set:

| Secret Name            | Purpose                                                                                                                                        | Required |
| ---------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | -------- |
{% if use_terraform %}
| `TF_API_TOKEN`         | API token for authenticating with Terraform Cloud. Generate one [here](https://app.terraform.io/app/{{ tfc_organization }}/settings/authentication-tokens). | ✅        |
| `CF_API_TOKEN`         | API token for authenticating with Cloudflare, used by Terraform to manage Cloudflare resources.                                                  | ✅        |
| `CF_ZONE_ID`           | Cloudflare Zone ID, specifying which domain or zone Terraform should manage.                                                                     | ✅        |
| `HCLOUD_TOKEN`         | Hetzner Cloud API token, allowing Terraform to manage infrastructure in Hetzner Cloud.                                                           | ✅        |
| `SSH_AUTHORIZED_KEY`   | Public SSH key used for provisioning and accessing cloud instances securely.                                                                     | ✅        |
| `SSH_PRIVATE_KEY`      | Private key matching `SSH_AUTHORIZED_KEY`, used by CI to connect to provisioned servers.                                                         | ✅        |
{% endif %}
{% if ansible_enabled %}
| `ANSIBLE_VAULT_PASSWORD` | Vault password, only needed once you add real encrypted `vault.yml` files (see `ansible/README.md`). A fresh project has none, so this can be left unset until then. | Optional |
{% endif %}
{% if use_terraform %}

Terraform-related secrets apply to both the `staging` and `production` environments. `plan` always runs both environments for visibility, but `apply` never touches both in the same run: pushing to `main` applies **production** only; applying `staging` (or re-applying `production` on demand) requires manually running the workflow (`workflow_dispatch`) and picking the environment. The `apply` job maps onto a matching [GitHub Environment](https://docs.github.com/en/actions/deployment/targeting-different-environments/using-environments-for-deployment), so you can set stricter protection rules (required reviewers, etc.) on `production`.
{% endif %}
